OL,6,FLabour Party chairwoman Anneliese
OL,7,FDodds said: "Lee Anderson's comments
OL,8,Fwere unambiguously Islamophobic,
OL,9,Fdivisive and damaging.
OL,11,F"It is right that he has had the whip
OL,12,Fremoved but the suggestion that Lee
OL,13,FAnderson would have retained the
OL,14,Fconfidence of the Prime Minister,
OL,15,Fsimply if he apologised, is deeply
OL,16,Fconcerning. These views are wrong,
OL,17,Ffull stop, and there shouldn't be
OL,18,Fconditions on removing them from your
OL,19,Fparty."
